value.value: The movement of a cellular component as a result of microtubule polymerization.

label.value: G-protein gated monoatomic ion channel activity

value.value: An ion channel activity that is gated by binding of a G-protein beta-gamma dimer.

label.value: G-protein gated monoatomic cation channel activity

value.value: A cation channel activity that is gated by binding of a G-protein beta-gamma dimer.
A potassium channel activity that is gated by binding of a G-protein beta-gamma dimer.

label.value: G-protein gated potassium channel activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Any G-protein gated potassium channel activity that is involved regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential.

Direct interaction with a channel (binding or modification), resulting in its opening. A channel catalyzes energy-independent facilitated diffusion, mediated by passage of a solute through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel.
Binds to and increases the activity of a potassium channel, resulting in its opening.

label.value: ion channel modulating, G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G protein-coupled receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds through activation or inhibition of an ion channel.

Modulates the activity of a channel via direct interaction with it. A channel catalyzes energy-independent facilitated diffusion, mediated by passage of a solute through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel.

label.value: ion channel regulator activity involved in G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Modulation of the activity of an ion channel via direct interaction with it as part of G protein-coupled receptor signaling.

label.value: potassium channel activator activity involved in G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Activation potassium ion channel activity via direct interaction with a potassium ion channel during G protein-coupled receptor signaling.

definition.value: Examples include G-protein beta-gamma complexes that bind to and activate potassium channels.

label.value: potassium channel activating, G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G protein-coupled receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds activation of a potassium ion channel.

label.value: microtubule polymerization based protein transport to cell tip cortex

value.value: The transport of a protein to the cortex of the cell tip, driven by polymerization of a microtubule to which the protein is attached.

A microtubule-based process that results in the transport of organelles, other microtubules, or other cellular components. Examples include motor-driven movement along microtubules and movement driven by polymerization or depolymerization of microtubules.
The transport of a protein driven by polymerization of a microtubule to which it is attached.

label.value: negative regulation of presynaptic cytosolic calcium concentration

value.value: Any process that decreases the concentration of calcium ions in the presynaptic cytosol.
A region of the chromosome, adjacent to the telomere (on the centromeric side) that contains repetitive DNA and sometimes genes. This region is usually heterochromatin.
The process in which the 5' end of a pre-tRNA molecule is converted to that of a mature tRNA.

label.value: protein transport along microtubule to cell tip

value.value: The movement of a protein along a microtubule to the cell-tip, mediated by motor proteins.
A microtubule-based process that results in the transport of proteins.

The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a non-reproductive fruiting body over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A non-reproductive fruiting body is a colonial multicellular structure consisting of co-operating unicellular organisms, some of which are spores. An example of such a process is found in Dictyostelium discoideum and Myxococcus xanthus colonies.
The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a fungal sorus over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A fungal sorus is a spore containing structure.

label.value: RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain binding

value.value: Binding to the C-terminal domain (CTD) of the largest subunit of RNA polymerase II. The CTD is comprised of repeats of a heptapeptide with the consensus sequence YSPTSPS. The number of repeats varies with the species and a minimum number of repeats is required for RNAP II function.
The regulated release of dopamine from the somatodendritic compartment (cell body or dendrites) of a neuron.
The regulated release of dopamine from an axon.
A protein kinase complex comprising a conserved PAK/GC/Ste20 family kinase, leucine rich repeat protein Sog2 family, which function as part of the cell shape network.

A protein complex acting as ligand of the transforming growth factor beta receptor complex, typically a homodimer of any of the TFGbeta isoforms. The precursor of TGFbeta proteins is cleaved into mature TGFbeta and the latency-associated peptide (LAP), which remains non-covalently linked to mature TGFbeta rendering it inactive. TGFbeta is activated by dimerization and dissociation of the LAP.
A protein complex capable of forming 2Fe-2S clusters in mitochondria. In humans it consists of ISCU, NFS1, LYRM4, NDUFAB1 and FXN.

label.value: cochlear outer hair cell electromotile response

value.value: A rapid, force generating length change of an outer hair cell in response to electrical stimulation. This occurs naturally as during hearing where it serves a source of mechanical amplification.
Binding to an estrogen.
Development of a sorocarp formed by aggregation of cells with different genotypes.
Development a structure consisting of multiple co-operating unicellular organisms of the same species, involving cells of more that one genotype.
Development of a non-reproductive fruiting body formed by aggregation of cells with different genotypes.

label.value: altruistic, chimeric, non-reproductive fruiting body development

value.value: Development of a chimeric, non-reproductive fruiting body in which cells of all genotypes have an equal chance of becoming a spore cell.
Development of a chimeric sorocarp in which cells of all genotypes have an equal chance of becoming a spore cell.
Any process during chimeric sorocarp development that increases by which a cell increases the number of spore cells sharing its genotype at the expense of cells of other genotypes.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins in the presynaptic actin cytoskeleton.
Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus from a protozoan.
Enables the transmembrane transfer of an ion by a channel that opens when ATP has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts on the intracellular side of the plasma membrane.
The actin cytoskeleton that is part of a presynapse.

label.value: regulation of exocytic insertion of neurotransmitter receptor to postsynaptic membrane

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of exocytic fusion of neurotransmitter receptor containing vesicles into the postsynaptic membrane.

label.value: extrinsic component of postsynaptic density membrane

value.value: The component of the postsynaptic density membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that are loosely bound to one of its surfaces, but not integrated into the hydrophobic region.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of synaptic vesicle docking.

label.value: regulation of postsynaptic neurotransmitter receptor internalization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endocytosis of neurotransmitter receptor at the postsynapse.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of postsynaptic specialization assembly, the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a postsynaptic specialization.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of postsynaptic density assembly, the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a postsynaptic density.

label.value: regulation of neurotransmitter receptor transport, endosome to postsynaptic membrane

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of neurotransmitter receptor from the postsynaptic endosome to the postsynaptic membrane in transport vesicles.

The vesicular release of serotonin from a presynapse, across a chemical synapse, the subsequent activation of serotonin receptors at the postsynapse of a target cell (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) and the effects of this activation on the postsynaptic membrane potential and ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol. This process encompasses both spontaneous and evoked release of neurotransmitter and all parts of synaptic vesicle exocytosis. Evoked transmission starts with the arrival of an action potential at the presynapse.
A synapse that uses serotonin as a neurotransmitter.

The vesicular release of noradrenaline (norepinephrine) a presynapse, across a chemical synapse, the subsequent activation of noradrenaline receptors at the postsynapse of a target cell (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) and the effects of this activation on the postsynaptic membrane potential and ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol. This process encompasses both spontaneous and evoked release of neurotransmitter and all parts of synaptic vesicle exocytosis. Evoked transmission starts with the arrival of an action potential at the presynapse.
